- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses a method for synthesizing models and strategies, which is a common problem in AI.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper addresses a problem in software engineering related to checking the satisfiability of formulae expressing the specification of a system to be implemented.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses a method for checking the satisfiability of formulae using SAT Modulo Monotonic Theories solvers, which is related to programming language theory.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses a method for synthesizing models and strategies, which can be related to machine learning.
